## Overview
After individual crate conformance is verified, we need integration tests that verify crates work together correctly. This includes common workflows like:
- Building TUI applications with bubbletea + lipgloss + bubbles
- SSH apps with wish + bubbletea
- Forms with huh + bubbletea
- Markdown display with glamour + lipgloss

## Integration Test Categories

### Category 1: Bubbletea + Lipgloss Integration
**Common Pattern**: Views that use lipgloss for styling

```rust
/// Test that lipgloss styles work correctly in bubbletea views
#[test]
fn test_styled_bubbletea_view() {
    struct StyledModel {
        style: lipgloss::Style,
        text: String,
    }

    impl Model for StyledModel {
        fn view(&self) -> String {
            self.style.render(&self.text)
        }
    }

    let model = StyledModel {
        style: Style::new().foreground(Color::Red).bold(true),
        text: "Hello".to_string(),
    };

    let view = model.view();
    assert!(view.contains("\x1b[31;1m")); // Red, bold ANSI
}
```

### Category 2: Bubbletea + Bubbles Integration
**Common Pattern**: Using bubble components in bubbletea apps

```rust
/// Test viewport inside bubbletea app
#[test]
fn test_viewport_in_app() {
    struct AppWithViewport {
        viewport: bubbles::viewport::Viewport,
    }

    impl Model for AppWithViewport {
        fn update(&self, msg: Msg) -> (Self, Cmd) {
            // Forward messages to viewport
            let (vp, cmd) = self.viewport.update(msg);
            (Self { viewport: vp }, cmd)
        }

        fn view(&self) -> String {
            self.viewport.view()
        }
    }

    // Test scrolling works through bubbletea message dispatch
}
```

